<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-834-826  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 834 826.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  Oct 1989 v110 n4 p73(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Healthy offices: hard to define, but we need them.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lexington, Anne.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Businesses are more concerned than ever with developing healthywork environments, whether from a productivity point of view or analtruistic motive.andP;  As work becomes more computerized, new healthhazards are appearing.andP;  Carpal tunnel disease, a wrist problemcaused by frequent bending of the wrist when hands are in thewrong position for typing, is reported to have afflicted 70,000workers in 1987.andP;  Ergonomics is a recent word that is being usedto refer to the study of the problems people have in adjusting totheir environment.andP;  Such problems as maintaining proper aircirculation, use of natural and artificial light, choosing theergonomic chair are discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ErgonomicsOffice AutomationWork EnvironmentDesignHealth Care.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>